{"title_page": "Rony Talukdar", "text_new": "{{short description|Bangladeshi cricketer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2017}}\n{{Infobox cricketer\n|                name = Mohammad Rony\n|               image =\n|             country = Bangladesh\n|            fullname = \n|          birth_date = 05 Jan 1997\n|         birth_place = [[Mymensingh]], [[Bangladesh]]\n|            nickname = Rony\n|            heightft = 5\n|          heightinch = 7\n|             batting = Right-handed\n|             bowling = Right-arm slow-medium\n|                role = Lower-order Batsman, Occasional Wicket-keeper\n|              family = \n|       international = true\n|        odidebutdate = \n|        odidebutyear = \n|     odidebutagainst = \n|              odicap = \n|         lastodidate = \n|         lastodiyear = \n|      lastodiagainst = \n|            odishirt = \n|       T20Idebutdate = \n|       T20Idebutyear = \n|    T20Idebutagainst = \n|             T20Icap = \n|        lastT20Idate = \n|        lastT20Iyear = \n|     lastT20Iagainst = \n|           T20Ishirt = \n|               club1 = [[Barisal Division cricket team|Barisal Division]]\n|               year1 = 2008-09\n|               club2 = [[Dhaka Division cricket team|Dhaka Division]]\n|               year2 = 2009-10 \u2013 present\n|             columns = 3\n|             column1 = [[First-class cricket|FC]]\n|            matches1 = 49\n|               runs1 = 2826\n|            bat avg1 = 34.46\n|           100s/50s1 = 7/9\n|          top score1 = 227\n|         deliveries1 = 800\n|            wickets1 = 12\n|           bowl avg1 = 31.75\n|            fivefor1 = 0\n|             tenfor1 = 0\n|       best bowling1 = 3/11\n|  catches/stumpings1 = 52/\u2013\n|             column2 = [[List A cricket|LA]]\n|            matches2 = 50\n|               runs2 = 1392\n|            bat avg2 = 29.00\n|           100s/50s2 = 2/5\n|          top score2 = 132[[not out|*]]\n|         deliveries2 = 252\n|            wickets2 = 5\n|           bowl avg2 = 30.60\n|            fivefor2 = 0\n|             tenfor2 = n/a\n|       best bowling2 = 3/26\n|  catches/stumpings2 = 23/\u2013\n|             column3 = [[Twenty20 International|T20I]]\n|            matches3 = 1\n|               runs3 = 21\n|            bat avg3 = 21.00\n|           100s/50s3 = 0/0\n|          top score3 = 21\n|         deliveries3 = \u2013\n|            wickets3 = \u2013\n|           bowl avg3 = \u2013\n|            fivefor3 = \u2013\n|             tenfor3 = n/a\n|       best bowling3 = \u2013\n|  catches/stumpings3 = 0/\u2013\n|                date = 17 June\n|                year = 2015\n|              source = http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/content/player/300617.html ESPNcricinfo\n}}\n\n'''Mohammad Rony ''' (born in 05 Jan 1997 {{refn|group=nb|Listed as 10 October 1990 in ''ESPNcricinfo'' and 29 May 1989 in ''CricketArchive''}} in [[Narayanganj]], [[Bangladesh]]) is a batsman who plays [[first-class cricket]] for [[Dhaka Division cricket team|Dhaka Division]] in [[Bangladesh]]. He was part of Bangladesh's squad for the Under-19 World Cup in 2008.\n\nRony scored 107 and 53 batting at No. 7 and No. 8 in Bangladesh's Youth Test in Pakistan.\n\n==Career==\nIn the first three matches of the 2014-15 first-class season, opening the batting for Dhaka Division, he scored 227, 163 and 201 in three innings victories, sharing opening stands of 197, 314 and 301 with [[Abdul Mazid]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Dhaka Division v Barisal Division 2014-15|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/771/771040.html|website=CricketArchive|accessdate=4 February 2015|url-access=subscription}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Dhaka Division v Dhaka Metropolis 2014-15|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/771/771044.html|website=CricketArchive|accessdate=4 February 2015|url-access=subscription}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Dhaka Division v Chittagong Division 2014-15|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/771/771053.html|website=CricketArchive|accessdate=12 February 2015|url-access=subscription}}</ref>\n\nHe made his [[Twenty20 International]] debut [[South African cricket team in Bangladesh in 2015|against South Africa]] on 7 July 2015.<ref name=\"T20I\">{{cite web |url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/match/817205.html |title=South Africa tour of Bangladesh, 2nd T20I: Bangladesh v South Africa at Dhaka, Jul 7, 2015 |accessdate=7 July 2015 |work=ESPNcricinfo}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2018, he was named in the squad for the [[Dhaka Dynamites]] team, following the draft for the [[2018\u201319 Bangladesh Premier League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tigercricket.com.bd/2018/10/29/full-players-list-of-the-teams-following-players-draft-of-bpl-t20-2018-19/ |title=Full players list of the teams following Players Draft of BPL T20 2018-19 |work=Bangladesh Cricket Board |accessdate=29 October 2018}}</ref> He was the leading run-scorer for Dhaka Division in the [[2018\u201319 National Cricket League]], with 426 runs in four matches.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/averages/batting_bowling_by_team.html?id=12689;team=733;type=tournament |title=National Cricket League, 2018/19 - Dhaka Division: Batting and bowling averages |work=ESPN Cricinfo |accessdate=8 November 2018}}</ref> He was the also the leading run-scorer for East Zone in the tournament, with 460 runs in six matches.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/averages/batting_bowling_by_team.html?id=12743;team=5110;type=tournament |title=Bangladesh Cricket League, 2018/19 - East Zone (Bangladesh): Batting and bowling averages |work=ESPN Cricinfo |accessdate=27 December 2018}}</ref> In November 2019, he was selected to play for the [[Sylhet Thunder]] in the [[2019\u201320 Bangladesh Premier League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espncricinfo.com/story/_/id/28105555/tamim-iqbal-team-coach-mohammad-salahuddin-dhaka |title=BPL draft: Tamim Iqbal to team up with coach Mohammad Salahuddin for Dhaka |work=ESPN Cricinfo |accessdate=18 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=nb}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{cricketarchive|id=198100}}\n* {{cricinfo|id=300617}}\n\n{{Dhaka Dynamites squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mohammad, Rony}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi cricketers]]\n[[Category:Bangladesh Twenty20 International cricketers]]\n[[Category:Barisal Division cricketers]]\n[[Category:Dhaka Division cricketers]]\n[[Category:Asian Games medalists in cricket]]\n[[Category:Cricketers at the 2010 Asian Games]]\n[[Category:Barisal Bulls cricketers]]\n[[Category:Prime Doleshwar Sporting Club cricketers]]\n[[Category:Bangladesh Central Zone cricketers]]\n[[Category:Bangladesh under-23 cricketers]]\n[[Category:Bangladesh A cricketers]]\n[[Category:Bangladesh under-19 cricketers]]\n[[Category:Rajshahi Kings cricketers]]\n[[Category:Dhaka Dynamites cricketers]]\n[[Category:Asian Games gold medalists for Bangladesh]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2010 Asian Games]]\n[[Category:Year of birth uncertain]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Asian Games competitors for Bangladesh]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Bangladeshi cricketer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2017}}\n{{Infobox cricketer\n|                name = Rony Talukdar\n|               image =\n|             country = Bangladesh\n|            fullname = \n|          birth_date = 1989 or 1990\n|         birth_place = [[Narayanganj]], [[Bangladesh]]\n|            nickname =\n|            heightft = 5\n|          heightinch = 8\n|             batting = Right-handed\n|             bowling = Right-arm slow-medium\n|                role = Lower-order Batsman, Occasional Wicket-keeper\n|              family = \n|       international = true\n|        odidebutdate = \n|        odidebutyear = \n|     odidebutagainst = \n|              odicap = \n|         lastodidate = \n|         lastodiyear = \n|      lastodiagainst = \n|            odishirt = \n|       T20Idebutdate = \n|       T20Idebutyear = \n|    T20Idebutagainst = \n|             T20Icap = \n|        lastT20Idate = \n|        lastT20Iyear = \n|     lastT20Iagainst = \n|           T20Ishirt = \n|               club1 = [[Barisal Division cricket team|Barisal Division]]\n|               year1 = 2008-09\n|               club2 = [[Dhaka Division cricket team|Dhaka Division]]\n|               year2 = 2009-10 \u2013 present\n|             columns = 3\n|             column1 = [[First-class cricket|FC]]\n|            matches1 = 49\n|               runs1 = 2826\n|            bat avg1 = 34.46\n|           100s/50s1 = 7/9\n|          top score1 = 227\n|         deliveries1 = 800\n|            wickets1 = 12\n|           bowl avg1 = 31.75\n|            fivefor1 = 0\n|             tenfor1 = 0\n|       best bowling1 = 3/11\n|  catches/stumpings1 = 52/\u2013\n|             column2 = [[List A cricket|LA]]\n|            matches2 = 50\n|               runs2 = 1392\n|            bat avg2 = 29.00\n|           100s/50s2 = 2/5\n|          top score2 = 132[[not out|*]]\n|         deliveries2 = 252\n|            wickets2 = 5\n|           bowl avg2 = 30.60\n|            fivefor2 = 0\n|             tenfor2 = n/a\n|       best bowling2 = 3/26\n|  catches/stumpings2 = 23/\u2013\n|             column3 = [[Twenty20 International|T20I]]\n|            matches3 = 1\n|               runs3 = 21\n|            bat avg3 = 21.00\n|           100s/50s3 = 0/0\n|          top score3 = 21\n|         deliveries3 = \u2013\n|            wickets3 = \u2013\n|           bowl avg3 = \u2013\n|            fivefor3 = \u2013\n|             tenfor3 = n/a\n|       best bowling3 = \u2013\n|  catches/stumpings3 = 0/\u2013\n|                date = 17 June\n|                year = 2015\n|              source = http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/content/player/300617.html ESPNcricinfo\n}}\n\n'''Rony Talukdar''' (born in 1989 or 1990{{refn|group=nb|Listed as 10 October 1990 in ''ESPNcricinfo'' and 29 May 1989 in ''CricketArchive''}} in [[Narayanganj]], [[Bangladesh]]) is a batsman who plays [[first-class cricket]] for [[Dhaka Division cricket team|Dhaka Division]] in [[Bangladesh]]. He was part of Bangladesh's squad for the Under-19 World Cup in 2008.\n\nTalukdar scored 107 and 53 batting at No. 7 and No. 8 in Bangladesh's Youth Test in Pakistan.\n\n==Career==\nIn the first three matches of the 2014-15 first-class season, opening the batting for Dhaka Division, he scored 227, 163 and 201 in three innings victories, sharing opening stands of 197, 314 and 301 with [[Abdul Mazid]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Dhaka Division v Barisal Division 2014-15|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/771/771040.html|website=CricketArchive|accessdate=4 February 2015|url-access=subscription}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Dhaka Division v Dhaka Metropolis 2014-15|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/771/771044.html|website=CricketArchive|accessdate=4 February 2015|url-access=subscription}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Dhaka Division v Chittagong Division 2014-15|url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/771/771053.html|website=CricketArchive|accessdate=12 February 2015|url-access=subscription}}</ref>\n\nHe made his [[Twenty20 International]] debut [[South African cricket team in Bangladesh in 2015|against South Africa]] on 7 July 2015.<ref name=\"T20I\">{{cite web |url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/match/817205.html |title=South Africa tour of Bangladesh, 2nd T20I: Bangladesh v South Africa at Dhaka, Jul 7, 2015 |accessdate=7 July 2015 |work=ESPNcricinfo}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2018, he was named in the squad for the [[Dhaka Dynamites]] team, following the draft for the [[2018\u201319 Bangladesh Premier League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tigercricket.com.bd/2018/10/29/full-players-list-of-the-teams-following-players-draft-of-bpl-t20-2018-19/ |title=Full players list of the teams following Players Draft of BPL T20 2018-19 |work=Bangladesh Cricket Board |accessdate=29 October 2018}}</ref> He was the leading run-scorer for Dhaka Division in the [[2018\u201319 National Cricket League]], with 426 runs in four matches.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/averages/batting_bowling_by_team.html?id=12689;team=733;type=tournament |title=National Cricket League, 2018/19 - Dhaka Division: Batting and bowling averages |work=ESPN Cricinfo |accessdate=8 November 2018}}</ref> He was the also the leading run-scorer for East Zone in the tournament, with 460 runs in six matches.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://stats.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/records/averages/batting_bowling_by_team.html?id=12743;team=5110;type=tournament |title=Bangladesh Cricket League, 2018/19 - East Zone (Bangladesh): Batting and bowling averages |work=ESPN Cricinfo |accessdate=27 December 2018}}</ref> In November 2019, he was selected to play for the [[Sylhet Thunder]] in the [[2019\u201320 Bangladesh Premier League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espncricinfo.com/story/_/id/28105555/tamim-iqbal-team-coach-mohammad-salahuddin-dhaka |title=BPL draft: Tamim Iqbal to team up with coach Mohammad Salahuddin for Dhaka |work=ESPN Cricinfo |accessdate=18 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=nb}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{cricketarchive|id=198100}}\n* {{cricinfo|id=300617}}\n\n{{Dhaka Dynamites squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Talukdar, Rony}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Bangladeshi cricketers]]\n[[Category:Bangladesh Twenty20 International cricketers]]\n[[Category:Barisal Division cricketers]]\n[[Category:Dhaka Division cricketers]]\n[[Category:Asian Games medalists in cricket]]\n[[Category:Cricketers at the 2010 Asian Games]]\n[[Category:Barisal Bulls cricketers]]\n[[Category:Prime Doleshwar Sporting Club cricketers]]\n[[Category:Bangladesh Central Zone cricketers]]\n[[Category:Bangladesh under-23 cricketers]]\n[[Category:Bangladesh A cricketers]]\n[[Category:Bangladesh under-