{"title_page": "Billy Joe Saunders", "text_new": "{{short description|British boxer}}\n{{EngvarB|date=April 2015}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2015}}\n{{Infobox boxer\n| name = Billy Joe Saunders\n| image = Bj Saunders.jpg\n| caption = Saunders in 2018\n| nickname = Superb<ref>[[Michael Buffer]] announcing Saunders prior to the [[David Lemieux (boxer)|David Lemieux]] fight.</ref>\n| weight = {{plainlist|\n*[[Middleweight]]\n*[[Super-middleweight]]\n}}\n| height = 5ft 11in<ref name=stats2019>[[BT Sport]] tale of the tape prior to the Shefat Isufi fight.</ref>\n| reach = 70+1/2 in<ref name=stats2019/>\n| nationality = British\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1989|8|30|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Welwyn Garden City]], [[Hertfordshire]], England\n| style = [[Southpaw stance|Southpaw]]\n| total = 29\n| wins = 29\n| KO = 14\n| losses = 0\n| draws = \n| no contests = \n| medaltemplates = \n{{MedalSport | Men's [[amateur boxing]]}}\n{{MedalCountry | {{ENG}} }}\n{{MedalCompetition | [[European Union Amateur Boxing Championships|EU Junior Championships]]}}\n{{MedalGold | [[2007 European Union Amateur Boxing Championships|2007 Warsaw]] | [[Welterweight]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition | [[Strandzha Cup]]}}\n{{MedalGold | [[Strandzha Cup|2008 Bulgaria]] | Welterweight}}\n{{MedalCompetition | [[2008 European Union Amateur Boxing Championships|EU Championships]]}}\n{{MedalGold | [[2008 European Union Amateur Boxing Championships|2008 Cetniewo]] | Welterweight}}\n{{MedalCompetition | Commonwealth Championships}}\n{{MedalGold | 2007 Liverpool | Welterweight}}\n}}\n\n'''Billy Joe Saunders''' (born 30 August 1989) is an English [[professional boxer]]. He has held world championships in two [[weight class (boxing)|weight classes]], including the [[WBO]] [[super-middleweight]] title since 2019, and previously the WBO [[middleweight]] title from 2015 to 2018. Saunders is the first boxer from the [[Romanichal|Travelling community]] to become a two-weight world champion. At regional level he held the [[European Boxing Union|European]], [[British Boxing Board of Control|British]], and [[Commonwealth Boxing Council|Commonwealth]] middleweight titles between 2012 and 2015. As an [[amateur boxing|amateur]], Saunders represented Great Britain at the [[2008 Olympics]], reaching the second round of the [[welterweight]] bracket. In the same year, he won gold at the [[2008 European Union Amateur Boxing Championships|EU Championships]].\n\nAs of December 2019, he is ranked as the world's second best active super-middleweight by [[BoxRec]] and sixth by ''[[The Ring (magazine)|The Ring]].'' On 19 December 2015 Saunders made history by competing in the first world title fight contested between two members of the travelling community when he fought [[Andy Lee (boxer)|Andy Lee]] for the WBO middleweight title.\n\nHe is not a good person.\n\n==Amateur career==\nSaunders won his first 49 amateur fights at senior level, including the 2007 Commonwealth Championships<ref>{{cite web|url=http://amateur-boxing.strefa.pl/Championships/CommonwealthChamps2007.html |title=CommonwealthChamps2007 |publisher=Amateur-boxing.strefa.pl |date= |accessdate=6 September 2011}}</ref> and the 2008 [[Strandzha Cup]], edging out Cuban [[Carlos Banteux]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.amateur-boxing.strefa.pl/Tournaments/Strandjata2008.html |title=Strandjata2008 |publisher=Amateur-boxing.strefa.pl |date= |accessdate=6 September 2011}}</ref> In 2008 Saunders qualified for the [[Boxing at the 2008 Summer Olympics|Beijing Olympics]] in the [[Boxing at the 2008 Summer Olympics \u2013 Qualification#Welterweight (-69kg)|welterweight division]] at the age of 18.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/olympics/7271994.stm |title=BBC SPORT &#124; Olympics &#124; GB boxers secure Beijing places |publisher=BBC News |date=1 March 2008 |accessdate=6 September 2011}}</ref> At the European area qualifier in [[Pescara]], Italy he beat [[2006 European Amateur Boxing Championships|European champion]] [[Andrey Balanov]] and [[Kakhaber Zhvania]], but lost in the semi-final to [[Oleksandr Stretskyy]] before beating Pavol Hlava\u010dka for the all-important third spot.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.amateur-boxing.strefa.pl/Championships/EuroOlyQual2008_1.html |title=European Olympic Qualifications \u2013 1 \u2013 Pescara, Italy |publisher=Amateur-boxing.strefa.pl |date= |accessdate=6 September 2011}}</ref>\nto become the first person from the [[Romnichal|British Romanichal]] community to qualify for the games.<ref>{{cite web|last=Dennis |first=Chris |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/olympics/boxing/7302418.stm |title=Bbc Sport |publisher=BBC News |date=18 March 2008 |accessdate=6 September 2011}}</ref>.\n\n[[Boxing at the 2008 Summer Olympics \u2013 Welterweight|In Beijing]] he beat [[Adem K\u0131l\u0131\u00e7\u00e7\u0131]] in the first round but lost to old foe Carlos Banteux in the second. He was subsequently suspended for \"lewd behaviour\", allegedly pertaining to an incident with a local woman during a pre-season training camp in France.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/olympics/boxing/7573809.stm |title=BBC SPORT &#124; Olympics &#124; Boxing &#124; Boxer Saunders protests innocence |publisher=BBC News |date=21 August 2008 |accessdate=6 September 2011}}</ref> In early December 2008 Saunders turned professional.\n\n==Professional career==\n\n=== Middleweight ===\n\n====Early career====\n[[File:Billy joe saunders - wembley 2011.11.05.jpg|thumb|Saunders in 2011]]\nSaunders made his professional debut on 28 February 2009 at the [[National Indoor Arena]] in Birmingham, against Attila Molnar. Saunders looked confident from the opening bell, landing hard combinations which quickly overwhelmed Molnar. In round two, a series of punches that landed flush on Molnar's chin caused the referee to stop the fight and save a dazed Molnar. Saunders won his second fight by second-round stoppage of Ronny Gabel and his third fight, also by second round stoppage, of Matt Scriven. On 9 October 2009, he went four full rounds to outpoint Alex Spitko. On 21 May 2011, he scored an impressive second-round knockout victory over Kevin Hammond.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://boxingnews365.com/boxing-results.html |title=Boxing Results and Boxing News |publisher=BoxingNews365 |date= |accessdate=6 September 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110911030642/http://www.boxingnews365.com/boxing-results.html |archive-date=11 September 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Saunders went on to score wins against Norbert Szekeres, Gary Boulden and [[Tony Hill (boxer)|Tony Hill]], the last of these giving him his seventh professional knockout victory and his first major regional title, the [[list of Commonwealth Boxing Council Champions#Middleweight|Commonwealth middleweight championship]], on 28 April 2012.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://boxingreplays.com/news/saunders-vs-chris-eubank-jnr-is-on |title=Billy Joe Saunders Next Fight |publisher=BoxingReplays |accessdate=4 October 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006150129/http://boxingreplays.com/news/saunders-vs-chris-eubank-jnr-is-on |archivedate=6 October 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> For his first defence of the title, on 1 June, Saunders went the full twelve-round distance (also a first) against veteran [[Bradley Pryce]], outpointing him comfortably. A then-undefeated [[Jarrod Fletcher]] was quickly dispatched in two rounds on 14 September.\n\nOn 15 December, Saunders fought [[Nick Blackwell]] for the vacant [[list of British middleweight boxing champions|British middleweight title]]. This turned out to be one of Saunders' first tough outings, as he was forced to go the full twelve rounds en route to a competitive [[unanimous decision]] victory on the judges' scorecards.<ref name=telegraph2014nov>Davies, Gareth A. (28 November 2014). [https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/othersports/boxing/11262056/Billy-Joe-Saunders-vs-Chris-Eubank-Jnr-where-the-fight-will-be-won-and-lost.html \"Billy Joe Saunders vs Chris Eubank Jnr \u2013 where the fight will be won and lost\"]. ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]''. [[Telegraph Media Group]]. Retrieved 29 November 2014.</ref> A pair of trouble-free fights came next, against tough slugger [[Matthew Hall (boxer)|Matthew Hall]] on 21 March 2013 and [[Gary O'Sullivan]] on 20 July, both of which also lasted twelve full rounds. 2013 concluded for Saunders with another tough fight on 21 September, this time against fellow British prospect [[John Ryder (boxer)|John Ryder]] in defence of the Commonwealth and British middleweight titles. Both fighters came in undefeated and fought for twelve competitive rounds, with very close scorecards all favouring Saunders.<ref name=telegraph2014nov/>\n\n====Saunders vs. Blandamura, Eubank Jr.====\n[[File:Billy joe saunders2 - wembley 2011.11.05.jpg|thumb|Saunders (right) vs. Gary Boulden, 2011]]\nIt would be almost another year until Saunders had his next fight. On 26 July 2014 he added to his title collection with an eighth-round knockout of [[Emanuele Blandamura]], earning him the [[list of European Boxing Union middleweight champions|European middleweight title]]. Immediately after the Blandamura fight, Saunders called out another undefeated British prospect and archrival [[Chris Eubank Jr.]]<ref>[http://www.boxingscene.com/saunders-if-chris-eubank-jr-pair-lets-fight--80419 \"Saunders: If Chris Eubank Jr. Has a Pair, Let's Fight!\"]. BoxingScene. Retrieved 29 November 2014.</ref> Prolonged negotiations ensued between Frank Warren and Eubank's team (led by his father [[Chris Eubank Sr.]]), with the highly anticipated fight eventually signed in October<ref>[[Frank Warren (promoter)|Warren, Frank]] (9 October 2014). [https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/general/boxing/frank-warren-column-dealing-with-chris-eubank-was-a-nightmare-but-weve-finally-got-billy-joe-saunders-vs-eubank-jr-signed-9785929.html \"Frank Warren column: Dealing with Chris Eubank was a nightmare but we've finally got Billy Joe Saunders vs Eubank Jr signed\"]. ''[[The Independent]]''. Retrieved 29 November 2014.</ref> and taking place on 29 November. All three of Saunders' titles were on the line, as well as being an eliminator for the [[list of WBO world champions#Middleweight|WBO world middleweight title]]. The rivalry and build-up was likened to [[Nigel Benn vs. Chris Eubank|the first fight between Nigel Benn and Chris Eubank]] in 1990.<ref>Dooley, Terence (29 November 2014). [http://www.boxingscene.com/looking-back-year-leading-up-benn-eubank--84784 \"Looking Back at The Year Leading Up To Benn-Eubank\"]. BoxingScene. Retrieved 29 November 2014.</ref> Saunders went on to defeat Eubank via [[split decision]]; two judges had scores of 115\u2013114 and 115\u2013113 for Saunders, with the third judge scoring 116\u2013113 for Eubank. Having secured his third defence of the British middleweight title, Saunders earned the [[Lonsdale Belt]] outright; he gave this to his father Tommy as a Christmas present.<ref>Gold, Alasdair (30 November 2014). [http://www.hertfordshiremercury.co.uk/8203-Billy-Joe-Saunders-admits-8216-learning-8217/story-24906930-detail/story.html \"Billy Joe Saunders admits he has 'more learning' to do after Chris Eubank Jr fight\"]. ''[[Hertfordshire Mercury]]''. [[Local World]]. Retrieved 12 August 2015.</ref>\n\n====Saunders vs. Lee====\nWith the win over Eubank, Saunders was in line for an opportunity to fight WBO world middleweight champion [[Andy Lee (boxer)|Andy Lee]]. In February 2015, Saunders and Warren accepted a 'step-aside' financial offer from promoter [[Lou DiBella]] in order for Lee to face [[Peter Quillin]] instead.<ref>Kim, Steve (3 February 2015). [http://www.boxingscene.com/dibella-offers-clarification-on-lee-saunders-scenario--87020 \"DiBella Offers Clarification on Lee-Saunders Scenario\"]. BoxingScene. Retrieved 7 February 2015.</ref><ref>[[Frank Warren (promoter)|Warren, Frank]] (7 February 2015). [http://www.boxingscene.com/frank-warren-on-saunders-shot-froch-kessler-more--87168 \"Frank Warren on Saunders' Shot, Froch, Kessler, More\"]. BoxingScene. Retrieved 7 February 2015.</ref> Warren said that he hoped for Lee to win that fight so that Saunders vs. Lee could be staged in the summer. At around the same time, due to his high ranking, Saunders also received an offer from the [[International Boxing Federation|IBF]] to fight for their vacant world middleweight title, but he reiterated his intention to follow the WBO route.<ref>Donovan, Jake (12 February 2015). [http://www.boxingscene.com/saunders-passes-on-ibf-ndam-wants-lee-quillin-winner--87355 \"Saunders passes on IBF/N'Dam, wants Lee-Quillin winner\"]. BoxingScene. Retrieved 26 February 2015.</ref> In June, Saunders vs. Lee was officially announced for the WBO world middleweight title.<ref>Dooley, Terence (2015-06-22). [http://www.boxingscene.com/andy-lee-saunders-special-night-says-booth--92667 \"Andy Lee-Saunders Will Be Special Night, Says Booth\"]. BoxingScene. Retrieved 2015-08-04.</ref> The fight was initially scheduled to take place in Lee's hometown of [[Limerick]] on 19 September, but was postponed and moved to [[Manchester]] on 10 October due to Lee suffering from a viral infection.<ref>Murphy, Darragh (12 August 2015). [http://www.sportsjoe.ie/boxing/bad-news-for-fight-fans-as-andy-lee-v-billy-joe-saunders-bout-in-serious-jeopardy/35677 \"Bad news for fight fans as Andy Lee v Billy Joe Saunders bout is moved to Manchester\"]. sportsjoe.ie. Retrieved 12 August 2015.</ref> On 1 September, yet another postponement arose due to Saunders receiving a cut in sparring.<ref>Donovan, Jake (1 September 2015). [http://www.boxingscene.com/lee-saunders-warren-wants-medicals-new-date--95329 \"Lee-Saunders: Warren Wants Medicals Before New Date\"]. BoxingScene. Retrieved 1 September 2015.</ref> The fight was subsequently rescheduled for 19 December.<ref>[http://www.boxingscene.com/andy-lee-billy-joe-saunders-set-december-19th--96791 \"Andy Lee-Billy Joe Saunders Set For December 19th\"]. BoxingScene. 10 October 2015. Retrieved 10 October 2015.</ref>\n\nOn 24 July, Saunders took a tune-up fight, weighing in at {{convert|173|lb|kg}}, near the [[light-heavyweight]] limit\u2014and stopped Yoann Bloyer in four rounds.<ref>Gilfoid, Scott (2015-07-24). [http://www.boxingnews24.com/2015/07/chisora-destroys-lobjanidze/ \"Buglioni defeats Castaneda; Saunders stops Bloyer; Chisora destroys Lobjanidze\"]. boxingnews24.com. Retrieved 2015-08-04.</ref> On 19 December, Saunders defeated WBO middleweight champion Andy Lee via majority decision to capture his first world title, with judges' scores of 114\u2013112, 115\u2013111, and 113\u2013113. In the third round, Saunders scored two knockdowns against Lee to build up an early lead on the scorecards. He then continued to outbox Lee using head movement and an accurate [[jab]] until the later rounds. At this point, Lee began to land more frequently with heavy punches of his own, but was too late to overcome the points deficit despite a strong finish in the final round.<ref>[[Ben Dirs|Dirs, Ben]] (2015-12-19). [https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/boxing/35125589 \"Billy Joe Saunders beats Andy Lee for WBO middleweight title\"]. ''[[BBC Sport]]''. [[BBC]]. Retrieved 23 December 2015.</ref>\n\nSaunders' first defence of the title was scheduled for 30 April 2016, against [[Max Bursak]] at the [[Copper Box]] in London. However, Saunders was forced to pull out due to a hand injury sustained in training. \"I'm bitterly disappointed. This is boxing and these things happen\", he said at the time.<ref>[http://www.skysports.com/boxing/news/12183/10241438/billy-joe-saunders-title-defence-off-due-to-hand-injury \"Billy Joe Saunders title defence off due to hand injury\"]. ''[[Sky Sports]]''. [[Sky (United Kingdom)|Sky]]. 13 April 2016. Retrieved 19 April 2016.</ref>\n\nOn 8 July, Saunders revealed that he would be fighting on 17 September, likely on the undercard of [[Canelo \u00c1lvarez]] vs. [[Liam Smith (boxer)|Liam Smith]] at [[AT&T Stadium]] in [[Arlington, Texas]], which would have been broadcast on [[HBO pay-per-view]] in the US. It was rumoured that this would set up a WBO middleweight title defence against \u00c1lvarez in December.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxingnews24.com/2016/07/billy-joe-saunders-fight-september-17/|title=Billy Joe Saunders to fight on September 17 \u2013 Boxing News|date=2016-07-08|language=en-US|access-date=2016-07-18}}</ref> However, [[Golden Boy Promotions]] vice president Eric Gomez told [[ESPN]] on 14 August that Saunders would no longer feature on the undercard due to him rejecting all of the opponents presented to him. Opponents supposedly brought forward by Golden Boy were [[Gabriel Rosado]], [[Curtis Stevens (boxer)|Curtis Stevens]], and [[Willie Monroe Jr.]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.espn.co.uk/boxing/story/_/id/17297018/billy-joe-saunders-canelo-alvarez-undercard-rejecting-all-possible-opponents|title=Saunders off Canelo card for rejecting opponents|access-date=2016-08-14}}</ref>\n\n====Saunders vs. Akavov====\nFrank Warren finally confirmed Saunders first title defence would be against WBO European middleweight champion [[Artur Akavov]] (16\u20131 7 KOs), ranked by the WBO at number 10. The fight was due to take place at the [[Motorpoint Arena Cardiff|Motorpoint Arena]] in Cardiff on 22 October live on [[BoxNation]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.frankwarren.com/billy-joe-saunders-to-face-artur-akavov-in-maiden-world-title-defence/?|title=Saunders to face Akavov in Maiden World title defence|date=2016-09-30|language=en-GB|access-date=2016-09-30}}</ref> The fight card was postponed to 26 November after Saunders suffered a muscle injury, along with his stablemate [[Liam Williams (boxer)|Liam Williams]] also suffering an injury during a sparring session.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/saunders-injured-again-ring-return-pushed-november-26--109709?|title=Saunders Injured (Again), Ring Return Pushed To November 26 \u2013 Boxing News|website=www.boxingscene.com|access-date=2016-10-13}}</ref> The fight was postponed again to 3 December due to transitional issues with Akavov getting into the UK, the fight then took place at Lagoon Leisure Centre in [[Paisley, Renfrewshire]], [[Glasgow]], [[Scotland]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxingnewsonline.net/billy-joe-saunders-world-title-defence-postponed-again/|title=Billy Joe Saunders world title defence postponed again|last=|first=|date=23 November 2016|website=BoxingNewsOnline.net|publisher=|access-date=24 November 2016}}</ref>\n\nSaunders started off slow, showing signs of ring rust. Up until round 5, Akavov was the aggressor and doing enough to take the rounds. In rounds 5, 6, 7 and 8, Saunders bounced back and hit combos landing power shots in the process. This seemed to have tired Saunders out for the last two rounds. The fight went the full 12 rounds. Saunders won on all scorecards claiming a unanimous decision to retain his WBO title. The three judges scored it 116\u2013113, 116\u2013112, and 115\u2013113 in favour of Saunders.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ringtv.com/475887-billy-joe-saunders-poor-decision-victory-artur-akavov/|title=Saunders poor in decision victory over Akakov|last=|first=|date=3 December 2016|website=The Ring|publisher=|access-date=3 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxingnewsonline.net/billy-joe-saunders-defends-wbo-middleweight-title/|title=Billy Joe Saunders defends WBO middleweight title|last=|first=|date=3 December 2016|website=boxingnewsonline|publisher=|access-date=4 December 2016}}</ref> Immediately following the announcement, Saunders took the microphone off the MC and thanked the live crowd for coming and harshly criticized himself on his performance, \"There was nothing there. I\u2019ve been out a year, a bit overweight. A few adjustments to camp. Just flat, really, really flat. I\u2019d like to apologise to the fans, especially who paid for it. Terrible performance.\" According to Compubox Stats, Saunders landed 85 punches of 579 thrown (14%), with 51 jabs landed and Akavov landed 81 of his 624 thrown (13%), this included 44 power punches.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/billy-joe-saunders-struggles-decision-win-over-artur-akavov-results--111387|title=Saunders struggles in decision win over Akavov|last=|first=|date=3 December 2016|website=Boxing Scene|publisher=|access-date=4 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.boxingscene.com/billy-joe-saunders-vs-artur-akavov-compubox-punch-stats--111391|title=Billy Joe Saunders vs. Artur Akavov - CompuBox Punch Stats|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2018-11-29|language=en-us}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 December, it was announced that Saunders had parted with long time trainer Jimmy Tibbs, who he had been mentored by since turning professional in 2008. Rumours had started when Tibbs was not present at Saunders last title defence against Akavov. Instead having Danny Vaughan, Johnney Roye and Ben Davison in his corner. Promoter Frank Warren officially confirmed the news.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/billy-joe-saunders-splits-with-jimmy-tibbs--111948|title=Billy Joe Saunders Splits With Jimmy Tibbs \u2013 Boxing News|website=www.boxingscene.com|access-date=2016-12-20}}</ref> On 18 January 2017, Saunders announced he would be working with [[Adam Booth]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.whtimes.co.uk/sport/boxing/billy_joe_saunders_links_up_with_trainer_adam_booth_1_4854221|title=Billy Joe Saunders links up with trainer Adam Booth|last=|first=|date=18 January 2017|website=|publisher=|access-date=18 January 2017}}</ref>\n\n====Cancelled Avtandil Khurtsidze fight====\nIn early February 2017, [[mandatory challenger]] [[Avtandil Khurtsidze]] (32-2-2, 21 KOs) took a 'step-a-side' fee to allow Saunders to pursue a bigger fight.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.ringtv.com/483777-khurtsidze-expected-take-step-aside-money-saunders/|title=Khurtsidze expected to take step-aside money for Saunders \u2013 The Ring|date=2017-02-07|work=The Ring|access-date=2017-04-24|language=en-US}}</ref> On 28 February, it was announced that Khurtsidze would fight British boxer [[Tommy Langford]] for the vacant interim WBO title in April.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.badlefthook.com/2017/2/28/14765290/avtandil-khurtsidze-to-face-tommy-langford-for-interim-wbo-title|title=Khurtsidze vs. Langford set for interim title|date=2017-02-28|website=Bad Left Hook|access-date=2017-04-24}}</ref>\n\nAfter retaining his belts against Jacobs, [[Gennady Golovkin]] stated that he wanted to unify the middleweight division and hold all the belts available. Golovkin said, \"My goal is all the belts in the middleweight division. Of course, Billy Joe is the last one. It is my dream.\" Rumors of the fight taking place in Golovkin's home country Kazakhstan in June during the [[Expo 2017|EXPO 2017]]. The last time Golovkin fought in his home country was in 2010.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/golovkin-billy-joe-saunders-last-one-it-my-dream--114767|title=Golovkin: Billy Joe Saunders is The Last One, It is My Dream! \u2013 Boxing News|website=www.boxingscene.com|language=en-us|access-date=2017-04-07}}</ref> On 20 March, Golovkin said that he would fight Saunders in his native Kazakhstan or the O2 Arena in London.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/london-could-stage-billy-joe-saunders-unification-fight-with-gennady-golovkin-a3493906.html|title=Billy Joe Saunders could fight Gennady Golovkin in London|date=2017-03-20|work=Evening Standard|access-date=2017-04-07|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n\nSaunders tweeted on social media that although he didn't watch Golovkin's fight with Jacobs, he was ready to fight him.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxnation.com/boxing-news/i-m-ready-saunders-wants-golovkin-unification/|title=\"I\u2019m ready!\" \u2013 Saunders wants Golovkin unification|website=www.boxnation.com|language=en|access-date=2017-04-08}}</ref> Saunders claimed to have signed the contract on his end and gave Golovkin a deadline to sign his.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.vitalboxing.com/article.asp?a=4640|title=Vital Boxing {{!}} Saunders Gives Golovkin a Deadline|last=Ltd|first=Vitalnetwork|website=www.vitalboxing.com|language=en|access-date=2017-04-08}}</ref> On 29 March, Frank Warren also stated that Golovkin would have ten days to sign for the fight.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/frank-warren-hits-golovkin-with-deadline-ink-saunders-deal--115085|title=Frank Warren Hits Golovkin With Deadline To Ink Saunders Deal \u2013 Boxing News|website=www.boxingscene.com|language=en-us|access-date=2017-04-08}}</ref> Saunders later claimed to have moved on from Golovkin, until Warren said the deal was still in place.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/saunders-promoter-we-not-moved-on-from-golovkin--115217|title=Saunders' Promoter: We Have NOT Moved On From Golovkin \u2013 Boxing News|website=www.boxingscene.com|language=en-us|access-date=2017-04-08}}</ref> Over the next week, Saunders continued to insult Golovkin through social media.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.boxingnewsandviews.com/2017/04/03/billy-joe-saunders-t-shirt/|title=Billy Joe Saunders T-Shirt Message For Gennady Golovkin \u2013 Boxing News|last=BoxingNewsAndViews|date=2017-04-03|website=Boxing News and Views|access-date=2017-04-08}}</ref> On 7 April, Warren told iFL TV, that Golovkin had a hand injury, which was the reason why the fight hadn't been made. In the interview, he said, \"At the moment, they\u2019re saying that Golovkin\u2019s injured. So we\u2019re waiting to see where this is all going. But as far as I\u2019m concerned, we agreed [to] terms.\" It was also noted that he would wait until 6 May, for any updates.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/warren-golovkin-injury-holding-up-getting-ggg-saunders-done--115379|title=Warren: Golovkin Injury Holding Up Getting GGG-Saunders Done \u2013 Boxing News|website=www.boxingscene.com|language=en-us|access-date=2017-04-08}}</ref> On 11 April, it was reported that the fight would not take place and Golovkin would ultimately focus on a September 2017 fight against [[Canelo \u00c1lvarez]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.cbssports.com/boxing/news/report-gennady-golovkin-to-skip-june-return-and-focus-on-canelo-alvarez/|title=Report: Gennady Golovkin to skip June return and focus on Canelo Alvarez|work=CBSSports.com|access-date=2017-04-12|language=en}}</ref>\n\nOn 22 April 2017, Khurtsidze knocked Langford out in round 5 with a left hook to secure his next fight against Saunders.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/boxing/39680275|title=Tommy Langford beaten as Avtandil Khurtsidze sets up Billy Joe Saunders bout|date=2017-04-22|work=BBC Sport|access-date=2017-04-24|language=en-GB}}</ref> A day later the fight between Saunders and Khurtsidze was discussed to take place at the Copper Box in London on 8 July 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/billy-joe-saunders-vs-avtandil-khurtsidze-on-july-8-copper-box--115905|title=Billy Joe Saunders vs. Avtandil Khurtsidze on July 8, Copper Box \u2013 Boxing News|website=www.boxingscene.com|language=en-us|access-date=2017-04-24}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 June, Khurtsidze was arrested in New York along with 32 others, linking him in a Russian and Georgian crime syndicate. Racketeer charges and conspiracy to commit fraud were the two alleged charges, promoter Lou DiBella said, whilst the fight wouldn't be completely called off, it would be postponed.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.ringtv.com/502229-khurtsidze-indicted-rico-charges-saunders-bout-postponed/|title=Avtandil Khurtsidze indicted on racketeering charges \u2013 The Ring|date=2017-06-08|work=The Ring|access-date=2017-06-11|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/boxing/40208313|title=Billy Joe Saunders bout cancelled after Avtandil Khurtsidze arrest|date=2017-06-08|work=BBC Sport|access-date=2017-06-11|language=en-GB}}</ref> Due to the fight being a mandatory defence, Saunders' promoter Frank Warren said that he was unable to make a voluntary defence, as such, taken off the card completely, although the rest of the card would still take place.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.frankwarren.com/saunders-v-khurtsidze-update/|title=SAUNDERS V KHURTSIDZE UPDATE|date=2017-06-09|work=Frank Warren|access-date=2017-06-11|language=en-GB}}</ref> On 20 June 2017 the WBO released a statement in which it said that the Interim WBO title would be vacated and that Khurtsidze's team would have 10 days to appeal the decision.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.espn.co.uk/boxing/story/_/id/19688203/jailed-avtandil-khurtsidze-stripped-interim-title|title=Jailed Khurtsidze stripped of interim title|work=ESPN.com|access-date=2017-06-21}}</ref>\n\n====Saunders vs. Monroe Jr.====\nOn 14 June 2017, Frank Warren announced that Saunders would likely make his second title defence in September 2017. Names in the running included [[David Lemieux (boxer)|David Lemieux]], [[Ry\u014dta Murata|Ryota Murata]] and [[Robert Brant|Rob Brant]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/warren-saunders-back-september-jacobs-highly-unlikely--117524|title=Warren: Saunders Back in September, Jacobs is Highly Unlikely \u2013 Boxing News|website=www.boxingscene.com|language=en-us|access-date=2017-07-05}}</ref> The plan was to have Saunders fight around the same week as [[Gennady Golovkin vs. Canelo \u00c1lvarez|Golovkin vs. \u00c1lvarez]], and then fight the winner. The date of Saunders defence was confirmed by Warren, to take place on 16 September.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/frank-warren-on-billy-joe-saunders-return-on-september-16--118042|title=Frank Warren on Billy Joe Saunders' Return on September 16 \u2013 Boxing News|website=www.boxingscene.com|language=en-us|access-date=2017-07-05}}</ref>\n\nOn 28 June, it was revealed that Saunders had parted ways with trainer Adam Booth, after working together for only six months, and joined Sheffield based trainer Dominic Ingle. Saunders claimed that the reason for the split with Booth was due to being 'too close to home' and ongoing distractions. Ingle confirmed the statement to Boxing News.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/billy-joe-saunders-drops-adam-booth-hires-dominic-ingle--117989|title=Billy Joe Saunders Drops Adam Booth, Hires Dominic Ingle \u2013 Boxing News|website=www.boxingscene.com|language=en-us|access-date=2017-07-05}}</ref> Lemieux admitted to passing on the opportunity to fight Saunders because he was pursuing a bigger money fight, possibly with [[Miguel Cotto]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/lemieux-admits-he-passed-on-saunders-eyes-set-on-cotto--118252|title=Lemieux Admits He Passed on Saunders, Has Eyes Set on Cotto \u2013 Boxing News|website=www.boxingscene.com|language=en-us|access-date=2017-07-07}}</ref>\n\nWarren announced on 6 July, that a deal was in place for Saunders to defend his title against former world title challenger [[Willie Monroe Jr.]] (21-2, 6 KOs) at the [[Copper Box Arena]] in London  on 16 September 2017. Monroe was coming off a unanimous decision win against [[Gabriel Rosado|Gabe Rosado]] on 17 September 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/billy-joe-saunders-fight-willie-monroe-jr-on-9-16-london--118241|title=Billy Joe Saunders to Fight Willie Monroe Jr. on 9/16 in London \u2013 Boxing News|website=www.boxingscene.com|language=en-us|access-date=2017-07-07}}</ref> At the press conference, Warren said the winner would highly likely be in a position to fight the winner of Golovkin and \u00c1lvarez. Monroe was said to be excited fighting outside of the US for the first time in his career.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.espn.co.uk/boxing/story/_/id/20087620/billy-joe-saunders-defend-middleweight-belt-willie-monroe-jr-september|title=Saunders to defend belt vs. Monroe in London|work=ESPN.com|access-date=2017-07-20}}</ref> Throughout the promotion, Saunders had tried to get the better of Monroe. This continued at the official weigh in. As Saunders stood on the scale, his 7-year-old son, Stevie Saunders, also took to stage. Monroe patted Stevie on the head, to which he reacted by punching and kicking Monroe to the groin. Banner Promotions Vice-President, Matt Rowland felt disheartened to Saunders 'non-reaction'. Monroe also had no immediate reaction to being hit on the groin.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.worldboxingnews.net/2017/09/15/news/monroe-promoter-disheartened-by-billy-joe-saunders-non-reaction-to-son-punching-willie-monroe|title=Promoter disheartened by Billy Joe Saunders 'non-reaction' to son punching Willie Monroe Jr.|last=Banner|work=WBN \u2013 World Boxing News|access-date=2017-09-16|language=en-gb}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.espn.co.uk/boxing/story/_/id/20712205/billy-joe-saunders-son-low-blows-willie-monroe-jr-weigh-in|title=Saunders' son punches, kicks Monroe Jr|work=ESPN.com|access-date=2017-09-16}}</ref> Monroe later reacted stating that he intended to sue unless he was compensated.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.punditarena.com/boxing/sraftery/willie-monroe-jr-threatens-lawsuits/|title=Willie Monroe Jr. Issues Angry Response To Incident Involving Billy Joe Saunders' Son \u2013 Pundit Arena|website=www.punditarena.com|language=en-GB|access-date=2017-09-16}}</ref> Saunders defeated Monroe via unanimous decision 117\u2013111, 115\u2013114, and 117\u2013112 on the cards respectively. Saunders controlled the fight throughout, suffering a cut over his right eye during a clash of heads in round 4. Monroe did not pose much threat and lack of knockout power, saw him on the backfoot, pot-shotting and using his jab frequently. In the post-fight, Saunders thanked Monroe for coming over to the UK for the fight, while his son apologized for hitting him in the groin. Warren stated that Saunders would likely fight again in December 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/billy-joe-saunders-decisions-willie-monroe-retains-results--120554|title=Billy Joe Saunders Decisions Willie Monroe, Retains WBO Belt \u2013 Boxing News|website=www.boxingscene.com|language=en-us|access-date=2017-09-20}}</ref>\n\n====Saunders vs. Lemieux====\nAlthough the [[Canelo \u00c1lvarez vs. Gennady Golovkin|Golovkin vs. Canelo fight]] ended in a split draw, Saunders still pursued a unification fight next.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/saunders-now-hoping-unification-with-golovkin--120614|title=Saunders Now Hoping To Have Unification With Golovkin \u2013 Boxing News|website=www.boxingscene.com|language=en-us|access-date=2017-09-20}}</ref> After weeks of going back and forth with former IBF champion [[David Lemieux (boxer)|David Lemieux]] (38-3, 33 KOs) on Twitter, on 10 October, the WBO ordered them to meet in a mandatory fight with both camps having 30 days to negotiate a fight, which would likely take place early in 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.espn.com/boxing/story/_/id/20980360/wbo-orders-middleweight-champ-billy-joe-saunders-fight-former-titlist-david-lemieux|title=WBO orders champ Saunders to fight Lemieux|work=ESPN.com|access-date=2017-10-12}}</ref> On 16 October, Lemieux's manager Camille Estephan stated the negotiations were going well for the fight and could possibly take place at the Bell Centre in Canada on 16 December 2017. He also stated that [[HBO]] were interested showcasing the fight.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/lemieux-vs-saunders-negotiations-going-well-december-16--121482|title=Lemieux vs. Saunders Negotiations Going 'Well' For December 16 - Boxing News|website=www.boxingscene.com|language=en-us|access-date=2017-10-16}}</ref> On 17 October, WBO confirmed the fight had been signed to take place at the new [[Place Bell (Laval, Quebec)|Place Bell]] in [[Laval, Quebec]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/saunders-vs-lemieux-deal-reached-december-16-hbo--121523|title=Saunders vs. Lemieux Deal Reached For December 16, HBO - Boxing News|website=www.boxingscene.com|language=en-us|access-date=2017-10-18}}</ref> Saunders deployed a strategic game-plan which worked out emphatically and exquisitely retaining his WBO title for the third time. The judges scored the fight 120\u2013108, 117\u2013111, and 118\u2013110. Both HBO and ESPN scored it a clear 120\u2013108 for Saunders. Saunders picked Lemieux off with shots as he would plod forward trying to connect with his big power shots. The difference in hand speed and skills were vast. Saunders used his movement and jab effectively. Lemieux was never able to catch up to Saunders to land his big power shots. In the post-fight, Saunders called out Golovkin, \"Golovkin, you keep saying you want my WBO belt. Fight me now. You'll be punching fresh air.\" CompuBox showed that Saunders landed 165 of 430 punches (38%) and Lemieux landed 67 of his 356 thrown (19%).<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/billy-joe-saunders-david-lemieux-results--123513|title=Billy Joe Saunders Makes Statement, Easily Dominates David Lemieux|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2017-12-18|language=en-us}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.espn.co.uk/boxing/story/_/id/21789382/billy-joe-saunders-cruises-unanimous-decision-win-david-lemieux-retains-middleweight-title|title=Saunders cruises to decision win vs. Lemieux|work=ESPN.com|access-date=2017-12-18}}</ref> Saunders earned a minimum $1 million purse while Lemieux took home a $500,000 guaranteed purse.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://tsmsportz.com/boxing/saunders-vs-lemieux-purse/|title=Saunders vs Lemieux Purse Payout 2017 (PPV Earnings)|date=2017-12-14|work=TSM Sportz - All About Sports|access-date=2017-12-18|language=en-US}}</ref> The fight, which marked Saunders' first appearance on HBO, averaged 716,000 viewers, peaking at 775,000 viewers.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/saunders-lemieux-peaked-775k-viewers-averaged-716k-on-hbo--123593|title=Saunders-Lemieux Peaked at 775K Viewers, Averaged 716K on HBO|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2017-12-20|language=en-us}}</ref>\n\n==== Inactivity ====\nOn 17 January 2018, Warren announced that Saunders would make a fourth defence of his WBO title at [[The O2 Arena]] in London, on the same card [[Terry Flanagan (boxer)|Terry Flanagan]] fights [[Maurice Hooker]] for the vacant WBO junior-lightweight title on 14 April. The bout would be a 'stay busy' fight for Saunders whilst Golovkin and \u00c1lvarez negotiate a rematch for May 2018. A few names listed as Saunders' potential opponents were [[Martin Murray (boxer)|Martin Murray]], Conrad Cummings, Rafael Bejaran and [[Jason Quigley (boxer)|Jason Quigley]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingnews24.com/2018/01/billy-joe-saunders-next-defense-apr-14-o2-arena/|title=Billy Joe Saunders\u2019 next defense on Apr.14 at O2 Arena \u00bb Boxing News|date=2018-01-17|work=Boxing News 24|access-date=2018-01-20|language=en-US}}</ref> Two days later, it was confirmed that 4-time world title challenger Murray (36-4-1, 17 KOs) would be Saunders next opponent, with the fight being billed as 'Battle of Britain' on [[BT Sport]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.boxingscene.com/billy-joe-saunders-vs-martin-murray-on-april-14-o2-arena--124433|title=Billy Joe Saunders vs. Martin Murray on April 14, O2 Arena|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2018-01-20|language=en-us}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://sport.bt.com/boxing/billy-joe-saunders-to-defend-his-world-middleweight-title-against-martin-murray-live-on-bt-sport-S11364244508224|title=Billy Joe Saunders to defend his world middleweight title against Martin Murray live on BT Sport|work=BT.com|access-date=2018-01-20|language=en}}</ref> On 20 March, Saunders suffered a hand injury in training forcing the card to be cancelled, however the fight was quickly rescheduled for 23 June 2018 at the same arena.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.frankwarren.com/saunders-injured/|title=SAUNDERS INJURED - Frank Warren|date=2018-03-20|work=Frank Warren|access-date=2018-03-20|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.skysports.com/boxing/news/12183/11298064/injured-billy-joe-saunders-postpones-wbo-title-defence-against-martin-murray|title=Injured Billy Joe Saunders postpones WBO title defence against Martin Murray|work=Sky Sports|access-date=2018-03-20|language=en}}</ref> On 3 June, Murray announced via his Instagram page that Saunders' had once again pulled out of the fight citing a hamstring injury. Saunders later tweeted, \"You have your ups in boxing, but last three months have been downs, sorry to Martin and the fans, be back soon.\" Murray was not convinced about the injury as he stated Saunders had long been after a big money fight with either Canelo \u00c1lvarez or Gennady Golovkin.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/boxing/44347293|title=Billy Joe Saunders withdraws from Martin Murray fight with injury|date=2018-06-03|work=BBC Sport|access-date=2018-06-04|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.worldboxingnews.net/2018/06/04/news/billy-joe-saunders-v-martin-murray-fallout-gets-bitter-with-venomous-social-media-exchanges|title=Billy Joe Saunders v Martin Murray FALLOUT gets BITTER with VENOMOUS social media exchanges|last=Murray|first=Saunders v|work=WBN - World Boxing News|access-date=2018-06-04|language=en-gb}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.boxingscene.com/murray-skeptical-saunders-injury-fight-postponed-again--128740|title=Murray Skeptical of Saunders\u2019 Injury; Fight Postponed Again|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2018-06-04|language=en-us}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 June, it was reported that Saunders would fight in September 2018. The then-IBF super-middleweight champion [[James DeGale]] was rumoured to be his opponent, possibly at 168 pounds.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.boxingscene.com/billy-joe-saunders-vs-james-degale-being-explored-sept-15--129294|title=Billy Joe Saunders vs. James DeGale Being Explored For Sept. 15|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2018-07-13|language=en-us}}</ref> On 12 July, the WBO ordered Saunders to make a mandatory defence against former two-time light-middleweight champion [[Demetrius Andrade]]  (25-0, 16 KOs), with both sides having 10 days to reach a deal.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.boxingscene.com/billy-joe-saunders-vs-demetrius-andrade-ordered-by-wbo--129898|title=Billy Joe Saunders vs. Demetrius Andrade Ordered By WBO|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2018-07-13|language=en-us}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.worldboxingnews.net/2018071224633/news/look-wbo-send-notice-ordering-billy-joe-saunders-v-demetrius-andrade-mandatory-within-ten-days|title=LOOK: WBO send notice ORDERING Billy Joe Saunders v Demetrius Andrade bout within TEN DAYS|last=Andrade|first=Saunders v|work=WBN - World Boxing News|access-date=2018-07-13|language=en-gb}}</ref> On 13 July, it was reported that Andrade would be unveiled as one of [[Eddie Hearn]]'s [[Matchroom Boxing|Matchroom Boxing USA]]'s signing with a deal that would see him fighting on DAZN. On 17 July, at the official launch, Andrade was introduced as one of Matchroom Boxing USA's signings.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.boxingscene.com/dazn-fighter-signings-event-dates-service-price-revealed--130041|title=DAZN Fighter Signings, Event Dates, Service Price Revealed|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2018-07-19|language=en-us}}</ref> On 25 July, the purse bid, which was scheduled for the evening, was cancelled after it was revealed that Eddie Hearn and Frank Warren had reached a deal for the fight to take place in USA under the Matchroom USA banner on [[DAZN]]. It was said that representatives of [[Top Rank]] were scheduled to be present at the purse bid to try and secure the fight for [[ESPN+]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.espn.com/boxing/story/_/id/24194220/billy-joe-saunders-demetrius-andrade-meet-fall-deal-reached|title=Saunders-Andrade deal made before purse bid|work=ESPN.com|access-date=2018-07-26|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.boxingscene.com/billy-joe-saunders-vs-demetrius-andrade-deal-reached--130291|title=Billy Joe Saunders vs. Demetrius Andrade - Deal Reached|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2018-07-26|language=en-us}}</ref> With Matchroom USA having promotional rights on the fight, Warren confirmed the fight would take place on [[Sky Sports]] in the United Kingdom and not [[BT Sport]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.worldboxingnews.net/2018072624901/news/frank-warren-confirms-billy-joe-saunders-v-demetrius-andrade-will-be-on-sky-sports-in-the-uk|title=Frank Warren confirms Billy Joe Saunders v Demetrius Andrade WILL FEATURE ON Sky Sports|last=Andrade|first=Saunders v|work=WBN - World Boxing News|access-date=2018-07-26|language=en-gb}}</ref> On 9 August, according to Hearn, the fight would take place at the [[TD Garden]] in [[Boston|Boston, Massachusetts]] on 20 October.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.boxingscene.com/saunders-andrade-headed-bostons-td-garden-on-october-20--130735|title=Saunders-Andrade Headed to Boston's TD Garden On October 20|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2018-08-09|language=en-us}}</ref>\n\nOn 27 September, [[ESPN]]'s [[Dan Rafael]] first reported that Saunders had tested positive for [[oxilofrine]], known as a [[stimulant]]. The test was carried out by the Voluntary Anti-Doping Association (VADA) on 30 August. VADA president Dr. Margaret Goodman reported, \"The results of the analysis are as follows: Adverse. Urine specimen number 4248408: oxilofrine detected. Note the following is also contained on the laboratory report: 'Opinions: oxilofrine may have resulted from the administration of ephedrine which was also detected but below the decision limit of 11ug/ml. The estimated concentration of ephedrine is 4.6 ug/ml.\" Hearn stated he would wait to see if the Massachusetts commission will allow Saunders to fight, however confirmed Andrade would still appear in the main event, whether it be a vacant world title or a non-title bout.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.espn.com/boxing/story/_/id/24815845/billy-joe-saunders-fails-drug-test-ahead-title-defense-demetrius-andrade|title=Saunders fails drug test ahead of Andrade fight|work=ESPN.com|access-date=2018-09-28|language=en}}</ref> Promoter Warren claimed the positive test was due to a nasal spray and was permitted by [[UK Anti-Doping|UKAD]]. The [[British Boxing Board of Control|BBBofC]] also stated Saunders was not in breach of their regulations.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.frankwarren.com/billy-joe-saunders-statement/|title=Billy Joe Saunders Statement - Frank Warren|date=2018-09-27|work=Frank Warren|access-date=2018-09-28|language=en-GB}}</ref> At a hearing, the MSAC denied Saunders a license, meaning he could not defend his title against Andrade. According to reports, the cancellation meant Saunders team would be losing around $2.3 million.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.boxingscene.com/billy-joe-saunders-denied-license-t-fight-andrade--132588|title=Billy Joe Saunders Denied a License, Can\u2019t Fight Andrade|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2018-10-10|language=en-us}}</ref> WBO president, Paco Valcarcel told ESPN, Saunders would not be stripped immediately, as Saunders would likely appeal and Andrade's fight against Namibian boxer Walter Kautondokwa (17-0, 16 KOs), who at the time was ranked #2 with the WBO, would be for the vacant WBO interim title. On 11 October 2018, it was announced that Saunders had vacated the WBO middleweight title in anticipation of being stripped.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.boxingscene.com/saunders-appeal-andrade-kautondokwa-interim-wbo-title--132590|title=Saunders To Appeal; Andrade-Kautondokwa For Interim WBO Title|work=BoxingScene.com|access-date=2018-10-10|language=en-us}}</ref>\n\n==== Ring return ====\nOn 12 December 2018, promoter Warren announced that Saunders would return to the ring on 22 December at the [[Manchester Arena]] on the [[Josh Warrington]] vs. [[Carl Frampton]] IBF featherweight championship undercard.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://britishboxingnews.co.uk/blogs/billy-joe-saunders-returns-on-warrington-frampton-card|title=Billy Joe Saunders returns on Warrington-Frampton card {{!}} British Boxing News|website=britishboxingnews.co.uk|access-date=2018-12-13}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/boxing/46542753|title=Billy Joe Saunders: Former world champion on Warrington v Frampton undercard|date=2018-12-12|work=BBC Sport|access-date=2018-12-13|language=en-GB}}</ref> It was later announced his opponent would be Hungarian boxer Zoltan Sera (32-17-1, 22 KOs).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/boxing/story/_/id/25516116|title=Saunders to return to action after nightmare year|date=2018-12-12|website=ESPN.com|language=en|access-date=2018-12-13}}</ref> Sera was replaced days before the fight. Saunders' new opponent was revealed to be 41 year old veteran [[Charles Adamu]] (32-13, 25 KOs) from Ghana.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.badlefthook.com/2018/12/20/18149923/warrington-vs-frampton-billy-joe-saunders-gets-new-opponent|title=Warrington vs Frampton: Billy Joe Saunders gets new opponent|last=Christ|first=Scott|date=2018-12-20|website=Bad Left Hook|access-date=2018-12-21}}</ref> Saunders weighed 178.5 pounds and Adamu came in at 173.2 pounds.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.boxingnewsandviews.com/2018/12/21/billy-joe-saunders-comes-in-heavy-for-short-notice-fight-on-frampton-vs-warrington-card/|title=Billy Joe Saunders Comes In Heavy For Short Notice Fight On Frampton vs Warrington Card|last=Doran|first=Niall|date=2018-12-21|website=Boxing News and Views|language=en-US|access-date=2018-12-21}}</ref> Saunders won the fight after Adamu failed to come out from his corner after round four.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.boxingscene.com/billy-joe-saunders-tommy-fury-get-wins-results--134857|title=Billy Joe Saunders, Tommy Fury Get Wins In Manchester|website=BoxingScene.com|language=en-us|access-date=2019-03-26}}</ref>\n\n=== Super-middleweight ===\n\n==== Saunders vs. Isufi ====\nOn 22 January 2019, the WBO lifted Saunders' six month suspension and ordered Andrade vs. Saunders for the WBO title.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.boxingscene.com/demetrius-andrade-vs-billy-joe-saunders-ordered-by-wbo--135616|title=Demetrius Andrade vs. Billy Joe Saunders Ordered By WBO|website=BoxingScene.com|language=en-us|access-date=2019-03-26}}</ref> On 18 February, Warren announced that Saunders would be moving up in weight and challenging for the vacant [[List of WBO world champions#Super middleweight|WBO super-middleweight]] title at the [[Wembley Arena|SSE Arena]] in London on 13 April. His opponent was scheduled to be German based Albanian Shefat Isufi.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.boxingscene.com/billy-joe-saunders-shefat-isufi-contend-vacant-wbo-title--136376|title=Billy Joe Saunders-Shefat Isufi To Contend For Vacant WBO Title|website=BoxingScene.com|language=en-us|access-date=2019-03-26}}</ref> A week later, [[Gilberto Ram\u00edrez]] stated although he was scheduled to fight at the light heavyweight limit for his next bout, he had not vacated his super-middleweight title. There would be a chance he could return to the super-middleweight division.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.boxingnews24.com/2019/02/gilberto-ramirez-wont-be-vacating-wbo-168-lb-title-after-all/|title=Gilberto Ramirez WON'T be vacating WBO 168 lb title after all|date=2019-02-23|website=Boxing News 24|language=en-US|access-date=2019-03-26}}</ref> Upon hearing this, Saunders admitted his fight was now in jeopardy and was not sure he would fight Isufi, if the WBO title was not at stake.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.boxingscene.com/billy-joe-saunders-admits-wbo-title-fight-doubt--136793|title=Billy Joe Saunders Admits \"WBO Title\" Fight in Doubt|website=BoxingScene.com|language=en-us|access-date=2019-03-26}}</ref>\n\nOn 12 March, it was reported that [[MTK Global]] had signed a deal with ESPN for them to broadcast 30 events a year. It was said that with this deal, Saunders' would be co-promoted by Top Rank.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.boxingscene.com/top-rank-add-saunders-warrington-frampton-maybe-dubois--137010|title=Top Rank To Add Saunders, Warrington & Frampton, Maybe Dubois|website=BoxingScene.com|language=en-us|access-date=2019-03-26}}</ref> It was rumoured around the same time that Saunders' had split with trainer Dom Ingle and may be trained solely by Ben Davison.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.boxingscene.com/billy-joe-saunders-splits-with-ingle-retain-ben-davison--137047|title=Billy Joe Saunders Splits With Ingle, May Retain Ben Davison|website=BoxingScene.com|language=en-us|access-date=2019-03-26}}</ref> On 25 March, at a press conference, Saunders vs. Isufi (27-3-2, 20 KOs) was announced to take place for the interim WBO super-middleweight title on 18 May at [[Stevenage]]'s [[Broadhall Way|Lamex Stadium]]. Warren believed the stadium would pack in around 15,000 fans seated on the stands and on the pitch.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/boxing/billy-joe-saunders-to-fight-shefat-isufi-at-stevenages-lamex-stadium-in-may-a4099871.html|title=Billy Joe Saunders to fight Shefat Isufi at Stevenage's Lamex Stadium in May|date=2019-03-25|website=Evening Standard|language=en|access-date=2019-03-26}}</ref> Saunders advised if he is victorious, he would likely challenge Ram\u00edrez for the full title in late 2019, however if Ram\u00edrez opted to remain at light-heavyweight, the winner of Saunders vs. Isufi would become full champion. Coming into the bout, Isufi was on a 10-fight win streak. The fight would air on [[BT Sport]] in the UK and streamed live on [[ESPN+]] in the United States.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/boxing/47691300|title=Billy Joe Saunders: WBO super-middleweight title fight moved to Stevenage|date=2019-03-25|access-date=2019-03-26|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.badlefthook.com/2019/3/25/18280810/saunders-isufi-interim-title-fight-official-for-may-18th|title=Saunders-Isufi interim title fight official for May 18th|last=Stumberg|first=Patrick L.|date=2019-03-25|website=Bad Left Hook|access-date=2019-03-26}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.espn.co.uk/boxing/story/_/id/26356003|title=Saunders bout vs. Isufi rescheduled to May 18|date=2019-03-25|website=ESPN.com|language=en|access-date=2019-03-26}}</ref> On 25 March, Saunders confirmed he would be training with Ben Davison full-time.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.worldboxingnews.net/2019/03/25/billy-joe-saunders-tyson-fury-ben-davison/|title=Billy Joe Saunders permanently links with Tyson Fury trainer Ben Davison|date=2019-03-25|website=WBN - World Boxing News|language=en|access-date=2019-03-26}}</ref> On 13 May, Ram\u00edrez officially vacated the WBO title, making Saunders vs. Isufi for the full world title.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.espn.com/boxing/story/_/id/26738044|title=Zurdo Ramirez vacates super middleweight title|date=2019-05-13|website=ESPN.com|language=en|access-date=2019-05-17}}</ref> Saunders came in at the 168-pound limit and Isufi came in slightly lighter at 167.4 pounds. Saunders won the fight by a landslide unanimous decision, winning the WBO super-middleweight title and becoming a two weight world champion. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.boxingscene.com/weights-saunders-168-isufi-1674-ready-wbo-title-clash--139098|title=Weights: Saunders (168), Isufi (167.4) Ready For WBO Title Clash|website=BoxingScene.com|language=en-us|access-date=2019-05-17}}</ref>\n\n==== Saunders vs. Coceres ====\n\nIn September 2019, it was announced that Saunders would make the first defence of his WBO super-middleweight title on the [[KSI vs. Logan Paul II]] undercard.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.boxingnews24.com/2019/09/billy-joe-saunders-makes-us-debut-on-blockbuster-ksi-vs-logan-paul-2-show/|title=Billy Joe Saunders makes US debut on blockbuster KSI vs. Logan Paul 2 show \u22c6 Boxing News 24|last=News|first=Boxing|date=2019-09-20|website=Boxing News 24|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-01}}</ref> On 9 October 2019, it was confirmed that Saunders would be fighting Marcelo Esteban Coceres on 9 November.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.espn.co.uk/boxing/story/_/id/27807826/billy-joe-saunders-defend-title-vs-marcelo-esteban-coceres-us-debut|title=Saunders to defend title vs. Coceres in U.S. debut|date=2019-10-09|website=ESPN.com|language=en|access-date=2019-12-01}}</ref> Coceres gave Saunders a tough fight through the first ten rounds, but in the eleventh, Saunders knocked Coceres down three times, prompting referee Ray Corona to wave the fight off 1 minute 59 seconds into the penultimate round,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://boxrec.com/media/index.php?title=Fight:2397225|title=Fight:2397225 - BoxRec|website=boxrec.com|access-date=2019-12-01}}</ref> securing the victory and successfully defending his WBO title.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/boxing/50364944|title=Billy Joe Saunders eyes Saul 'Canelo' Alvarez after Marcelo Esteban Coceres win|date=2019-11-10|access-date=2019-12-01|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n\n==== Saunders vs. \u00c1lvarez ====\n{{Main|Canelo \u00c1lvarez vs. Billy Joe Saunders}}\nOn 29 February, [[Canelo \u00c1lvarez]]' trainer Eddy Reynoso confirmed Saunders as the next opponent for the Mexican on 2 May, with a contract still to be finalised.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/boxing/canelo-alvarez-next-fight-billy-joe-saunders-callum-smith-opponent-a9367046.html|title=Canelo\u2019s coach confirms Saunders next for Mexican superstar|last=Rathborn|first=Jack|date=1 Mar 2020|website=The Independent|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=4 Mar 2020}}</ref> Both undefeated super-middleweight champions Saunders and [[Callum Smith]] had both turned down offers to fight \u00c1lvarez, hoping to bargain for a better purse to fight the pound-for-pound star.<ref>{{Cite news|last=|first=|url=https://www.givemesport.com/1551521-dazn-is-finally-set-to-launch-in-the-uk-with-billy-joe-saunders-v-canelo-alvarez-fight|title=DAZN is finally set to launch in the UK with Billy Joe Saunders v Canelo Alvarez fight win|date=2020-03-03|work=Give Me Sport|access-date=2020-03-03|url-status=live|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n\nThe fight was set to mark [[DAZN]]'s global launch in Latin America (including Mexico), UK, and 189 other countries after previously being launched in nine countries. The bout was postponed due to the spread of the [[Wuhan coronavirus]], while Canelo's team floated the possibility of a Golovkin trilogy late in 2020 that might conflict with the Saunders fight.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.worldboxingnews.net/2020/03/26/billy-joe-saunders-canelo-black-eye/|title=WATCH: Billy Joe Saunders confirms Canelo fight 'will happen - 100%'|date=2020-03-26|website=WBN - World Boxing News|language=en|access-date=2020-03-28}}</ref>\n\n====Suspension====\nOn 30 March 2020 Saunders had his boxing licence suspended by the British Boxing Board of Control (BBBofC) after sharing a video during the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United Kingdom|coronavirus pandemic]] that promoted [[domestic violence]]. In it, he used a punchbag to demonstrate how men could hit their female partners for \"giving you mouth\" during the shutdown.<ref>{{cite news |title=Billy Joe Saunders has boxing licence suspended after domestic abuse 'advice' video |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/boxing/52092520 |accessdate=30 March 2020 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=30 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Outside of boxing==\nA video of Saunders taunting a drug addict, offering \u00a3150 of crack cocaine to perform a sex act or punch a passer-by while he sat in his Rolls-Royce, was released on 17 September 2018. The woman punched a man walking past and a friend of Billy Joe's filmed the incident of which he then drove away from. There was no indication that Saunders had drugs in his possession, a second video then surfaced of him calling another woman \"a prostitute\", and stating \"we don\u2019t wanna get the clap off you\". The General Secretary of the [[British Boxing Board of Control]], Robert Smith, responded: \"I have just seen the videos and I can tell you we find it disgusting. I am speaking to members of the board now. I am keen to get on with this as soon as possible.\" The incidents were investigated.<ref>https://www.telegraph.co.uk/boxing/2018/09/17/billy-joe-saunders-taunts-female-drug-addict-disgusting-video/</ref><ref>https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/boxing/billy-joe-saunders-demands-woman-13261305</ref> And the BBBofC found Saunders 'guilty of bringing the sport into disrepute', issued Saunders a severe reprimand and fined him \u00a3100,000.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/boxing/45639675|title=Billy Joe Saunders: World champion fined \u00a3100,000 for 'sickening' video|date=2018-09-25|work=BBC Sport|access-date=2018-09-25|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2020, Saunders was alleged to have made a \u2018phone call to [[Delta Airlines]] claiming that three other boxers on a flight from [[Las Vegas]] to [[New York City| New York]] were infected with the [[Coronavirus]] associated with the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]. The call resulted in the three boxers being removed from the flight. An audio clip of the call circulated on social media in which Saunders was heard laughing about the incident. <ref>https://talksport.com/sport/boxing/685409/billy-joe-saunders-apologises-coronavirus-josh-taylor-ben-davison/</ref><ref>https://metro.co.uk/2020/03/20/billy-joe-saunders-speaks-coronavirus-prank-call-got-fellow-boxer-thrown-off-plane-12433164/</ref><ref>https://presstories.com/2020/03/21/billy-joe-saunders-coronavirus-farce-sees-josh-taylor-and-ben-davison-take-off/</ref>\n\nIn March 2020, Saunders posted an online video showing men how to hit their female partners whilst in [[Isolation (health care)|isolation]] due to the Coronavirus pandemic. In the video Saunders uses a punch bag to explain how to react if \"your old woman is giving you mouth\" and showing how to \"hit her on the chin\". He later posted a follow-up video to apologise for any offence caused.<ref>https://www.expressandstar.com/sport/uk-sports/2020/03/28/billy-joe-saunders-says-sorry-after-clip-of-him-teaching-men-how-to-hit-partners/</ref><ref>https://www.itv.com/news/anglia/2020-03-29/boxer-billy-joe-saunders-apologises-following-domestic-violence-advice-video/</ref><ref>https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2020/mar/28/billy-joe-saunders-apologises-for-video-giving-advice-on-hitting-women</ref><ref>https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/boxing/52082246</ref>\n\n==Professional boxing record==\n{{BoxingRecordSummary\n|draws=\n|nc=\n|ko-wins=14\n|ko-losses=0\n|dec-wins=15\n|dec-losses=\n|dq-wins=\n|dq-losses=\n}}\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:95%\"\n|-\n!{{abbr|No.|Number}}\n!Result\n!Record\n!Opponent\n!Type\n!Round, time\n!Date\n!Location\n!Notes\n|-\n|29\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|29\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|ARG}} Marcelo Esteban Coceres\n|TKO\n|11 (12), {{small|1:59}}\n|[[KSI vs. Logan Paul 2|9 Nov 2019]]\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|USA}} {{small|[[Staples Center]], [[Los Angeles, California]], US}}\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{small|Retained WBO super-middleweight title}}\n|-\n|28\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|28\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|GER}} Shefat Isufi\n|UD\n|12\n|18 May 2019\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|UK}} {{small|[[Lamex Stadium]], [[Stevenage]], England}}\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{small|Won vacant [[list of WBO world champions #Super middleweight|WBO super-middleweight title]]}}\n|-\n|27\n|{{yes2}}Win\n|27\u20130\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|GHA}} [[Charles Adamu]]\n|RTD\n|4 (8), {{small|3:00}}\n|22 Dec 2018\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{flagicon|UK}} {{small|Manchester Arena, Manchester, England}}\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|\n|-\n|26\n|{